quran[15]{c,v,t}:
  50,1,"Qāf. By the Glorious Qur’an!"
  50,2,"But they wonder that a warner has come to them from among themselves, so the disbelievers say, “This is something strange!"
  50,3,"What! Is it when we die and become dust [will we return to life]? That is a far-fetched return.”"
  50,4,"We certainly know what the earth consumes of them [after their death], and with Us is a Preserved Record."
  50,5,"Rather they rejected the truth when it came to them, so they are in a state of confusion."
  50,6,"Have they not then looked at the sky above them – how We built it and adorned it [with stars], and it has no rifts?"
  50,7,"And We have spread out the earth and set therein firm mountains, and caused to grow therein plants of every pleasant kind,"
  50,8,"as a source of insight and a reminder to every slave who turns [to Allah]."
  50,9,"And We send down from the sky blessed rain, with which We cause to grow gardens and grain for harvest,"
  50,10,"and towering palm trees having clustered fruit,"
  50,11,"as a provision for people, and We revive thereby a dead land; likewise will be the resurrection."
  50,12,"The people of Noah rejected [the truth] before them, as well as the companions of the Well and Thamūd,"
  50,13,"and so did ‘Ād, Pharaoh, the people of Lot,"
  50,14,"and the dwellers of the Forest, and the people of Tubba‘. All of them rejected the messengers, so My warning was fulfilled."
  50,15,"Were We wearied by their first creation? No indeed, yet they are in confusion concerning the second creation."